We used AISMR data from the Indian Institute of Tropical Meteorology (IITM) to represent the variability of the Indian summer monsoon rainfall (June to September). This dataset was derived from the area-weighted average of 306 rain-gauge stations that are almost uniformly distributed throughout India (
 
  50
 ). To confirm the reliability of the IITM data, we also used rainfall datasets from the Climatic Research Unit Time Series (0.5° × 0.5°;CRU TS v4.00) (
 
  51
 ) and the Global Precipitation Climatology Centre (0.5° × 0.5°; GPCC v7) (
 
  52
 ).
